Package com.edugility.objexj.engine

Contains the inner workings of the objexj toolkit.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ThreadScheduler<T> An interface indicating that implementations are capable of scheduling Threads.
 

Class Summary
BeginInput<T> An Instruction that advances the program counter if and only if an InstructionContext is at the beginning of the input.
CaptureGroup<T> A sub-List of items as captured by a Thread.
EndInput<T> An Instruction that advances the program counter if and only if an InstructionContext is at the end of the input.
Engine<T> A stateless regular-expression-processing virtual machine made to run Programs against Lists of input using Threads.
Filter<T> An Instruction that advances an InstructionContext's program counter if the InstructionContext can be read from and produces an Object that is non-null.
InstanceOfMVELFilter<T> An MVELFilter that conveniently checks the current item to see if it is an instance of a specified Class before applying further MVEL-based filters to it.
Instruction<T> An instruction run in the context of a thread of execution in an objexj virtual machine.
InstructionContext<T> A context inside of which an Instruction is executed.
Jump<T> An Instruction that causes an InstructionContext to jump to a new location in a Program.
Match<T> An Instruction that causes an InstructionContext to be placed into the match state.
MatchResult<T> The result of a Thread that has successfully matched its input.
MVELFilter<T> A Filter that implements its MVELFilter.accept(InstructionContext) method by running a user-supplied MVEL script against the InstructionContext's current Object.
Program<T> A LinkedList of Instructions that can be run by an Engine via a Thread.
ProgramCounter<T> A marriage of a Program and an index into that Program, and hence also an Iterator and Iterable of Instructions.
Save<T> An Instruction that saves the current item pointer in an InstructionContext so that later a capture group may be identified.
Split<T> A Jump instruction that also schedules a new Thread for execution at a different program location.
Stop<T> An Instruction that stops saving a capture group by calling InstructionContext.stop(Object) followed by InstructionContext.advanceProgramCounter().
Thread<T> A virtual thread for running Instructions from a regular expression Program.
 

Enum Summary
Thread.State An enum representing the possible states a Thread can be in.
 

Exception Summary
InvalidProgramCounterException An IllegalStateException indicating that a ProgramCounter was invalid.
 

Package com.edugility.objexj.engine Description

Contains the inner workings of the objexj toolkit. End users should focus on the com.edugility.objexj package instead.
